
Overview of noun pearl

The noun pearl has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) pearl -- (a smooth lustrous round structure inside the shell of a clam or oyster; much valued as a jewel)
2. (1) bone, ivory, pearl, off-white -- (a shade of white the color of bleached bones)
3. drop, bead, pearl -- (a shape that is spherical and small; "he studied the shapes of low-viscosity drops"; "beads of sweat on his forehead")

